Problematic assumption: The claim assumes that the bombing was specifically intended to stop an AT&T audit and cover up election corruption, without any concrete evidence to support this assumption.
Exaggerate: The claim exaggerates the significance of the Nashville bombing by linking it to a larger conspiracy involving election corruption and the Dominion software.
Contradict fact: The claim contradicts the fact that there is no evidence to suggest the explosion was election-related and that both AT&T and Dominion have denied the existence of an audit.
